{{Noticebox/Community}}
{{Stub}}'''Music culture''', and '''dance culture''' have a prominent scene in VRChat. The music scene includes community-created, and VRChat-partnered music events, and groups taking place in real time, inside of [[Worlds|worlds]] designed as nightclubs or venues, to mimic the feeling of being at a similar venue in real life.

In these events, VRChat users designate themselves as [[Wikipedia:Disc_jockey|disc jockeys]] (DJs), who can control physical DJ hardware, and simultaneously broadcast their DJ mixes into the world via [[Open Sound Control]], or dedicated hardware, often using livestreaming services like [[Trusted URLs|Twitch, or VRCDN]], in conjunction with a [[Video players|video player]]. In contrast, attendees come to listen to the music, and dance to it, sometimes with [[Full-Body Tracking|full-body tracking]] (FBT) peripherals, to move their legs and other limbs.

Some music events can also include live singing, karaoke, and group dancing.

== Dancing, and full-body tracking (FBT) ==
<small>''See also [[Full-Body Tracking]] for more detailed information.''</small>
[[File:RadianceCabaret_Dancer.webp|thumb|A user performs an elaborate dance at The Radiance Cabaret.]]
Users in VRChat can make their avatar dance by either applying animations on an [[Avatars|avatar]] when uploading it with the [[VRChat SDK]], or by physically dancing while in VR. Users are able to move around their head, and hands. Leg movement by default, is very limited - however, users can acquire and connect [[Full-Body Tracking|full-body tracking]] peripherals to VRChat, to move more of their body around.

Choosing to dance solo, at events with friends, or putting on a dance performance is entirely up to you! There are also worlds that can guide you with dance moves if you're unsure where to start. Additionally, there are [https://vrchat.com/home/search/worlds/MMD MMD worlds] that will synchronize your avatar dancing to a song.

== DJ'ing in VRChat ==
''<small>See also [[Guides:DJing in VRChat]] for more detailed information.</small>''

Disc jockeys are able to use DJ software with a [[wikipedia:MIDI|MIDI]] controller, or dedicated hardware to mix music, and play it for VRChat users. Ideally, users who DJ will choose to stream their music through a video player, which additionally allows the DJ to add visuals to the screen.

== Venues and communities ==
[[File:VRChat_VirtualEvents.webp|thumb|There are several music events that can be found in VRChat.]]
Exploring music [[events]], and utilizing the [[calendar]] can help you find music to listen and dance to. Within the [[Main Menu|Live Now]] tab on the Main Menu, you can explore 'Music & Performances' that are happening, and upcoming.
